		<link>https://ventureburn.com/counterpart-raises-50m-for-ai-insurance-coverage/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 11:47:09 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200427</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Counterpart, a specialty insurance carrier and the creator of &#8220;Agentic Insurance&#8221;, today announced the completion of a $50 million Series C financing round from Valor Equity Partners, a prolific and</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/counterpart-raises-50m-for-ai-insurance-coverage/" data-wpel-link="internal">Counterpart Raises $50M for AI Insurance Coverage</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://yourcounterpart.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Counterpart</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, a specialty insurance carrier and the creator of &#8220;Agentic Insurance&#8221;, today announced the completion of a $50 million Series C </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/all3-secures-25m-for-ai-powered-construction-robots/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">financing </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round from Valor Equity Partners, a prolific and early investor in both SpaceX and Tesla, among other firms, and an existing investor, Vy Capital.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The infusion of capital brings Counterpart&#8217;s total funding to $106 million at a time when American workers are entering a new frontier of litigation as small businesses (SBMs) embrace artificial intelligence in day-to-day operations.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The New Litigation Frontier: AI and Labor</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Counterpart&#8217;s own data states that the United States is now experiencing one of the most litigious periods in history. During fiscal year 2025, the EEOC received a then-record 270,000 pre-litigation enquiries and settled over $528 million.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">One key factor behind this fast growth is termed the &#8220;AI inflexion point&#8221;. Although almost 76% of SMBs use AI tools, only a few of them have formal policies for their management. This has caused an increase in claims such as:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Biased algorithm</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Machine learning software may unintentionally favour certain protected classes over others.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Content infringement</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Liabilities arising from responses by the AI for marketing or customer service which are questionably infringing.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Misclassification</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Mistakes in using the computer to run payroll or benefits.</span></li>
</ul>
<div id="attachment_200433" style="width: 590px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200433" class="wp-image-200433" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Counterpart.jpg" alt="Counterpart" width="580" height="163" /><p id="caption-attachment-200433" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Counterpart</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;We are entering a new generation of entrepreneurs navigating a minefield of legal liabilities without armour,&#8221; counters Tanner Hackett, CEO and founder of Counterpart. &#8220;Legacy insurance markets are not set up to underwrite or price these risks because they have very old-fashioned frameworks to deal with emerging ones. We designed Counterpart to be the parachute of the AI era.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/all3-secures-25m-for-ai-powered-construction-robots/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">All3 Secures $25M for AI-Powered Construction Robots</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Agentic Insurance: Moving Beyond the Policy</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Counterpart’s growth, which comes along with a $1.75B premium boost in 2025, is credited to its platform named &#8220;Agentic Insurance&#x2122;&#8221;. Counterpart&#8217;s platform is not a 1-year cycle, unlike most carriers, but has an AI-powered underwriting process that is on a continuous risk-management modus.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Handling over 250,000 applications via a network of 2,800 brokers, the company has built models which accurately forecast claims. This is how Counterpart manages to clear claims 2 x quicker and often 10% better for the insured business.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Series C funds are earmarked for four strategic pillars:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Product expansion</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Create new speciality lines focused on all errors and omissions produced by AI.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Industry Programs</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Development of paper plans for specialized verticals with high segment risk (such as acute and chronic health insurance, workers&#8217; compensation, and commercial construction).</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Claims Innovation</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Enhancements to the AI-led claims management platform to enable proactive legal advice.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Risks to Keep</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Agree to collateralise the &#8220;Counterpart Insurance Company&#8221; so that the firm can retain some of its own risks and negotiate directly with traditional reinsurers.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Backing of Heavyweights</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Valor Equity Partners, the lead investor, said that Counterpart’s early investment in AI-specific liability has put them ahead of the pack. Jon Shulkin, Partner at Valor Equity Partners, said that &#8220;Counterpart saw the AI inflexion coming years before the market.&#8221; &#8220;Their ability to turn every policy and every claim into data that makes the next customer’s experience better is transformative.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Though two strong lead carriers, Aspen, Markel and Westfield Specialty totally support Counterpart, the company is among the most well-capitalised &#8220;InsurTech&#8221; firms by the end of the first half of 2026.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/counterpart-raises-50m-for-ai-insurance-coverage/" data-wpel-link="internal">Counterpart Raises $50M for AI Insurance Coverage</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
